**Зарплата:** 4000 – 7000 €/месяц

**Формат:** Удалённо, Фултайм, Senior

**Стек:** DSP AdTech RecSys

**О компании**
We are a fast-growing tech company operating in the international programmatic advertising market. Our core product is a **Demand Side Platform (DSP)** capable of handling **50,000 queries per second** and delivering **20 million ad impressions per day**.

Our primary focus is on developing **smart bidding algorithms** that optimize ad auctions and maximize campaign efficiency. We work with both **In-App** and **web advertising**, covering a variety of geographic markets.

**Обязанности**
- Developing new machine learning models to improve traffic acquisition;
- Maintaining, tuning, and developing existing models;
- Conducting experiments on adding new factors to models, as well as measuring quality gains;
- Analyzing advertising statistics, searching for insights, and evaluating the results of the models;
- Customizing the parameters of advertising campaigns to link them to ML models;
- Interacting on tasks with the team: Developer, Data Engineer, DevOps, BI.

**Требования**
- Has experience in AdTech or in RecSys
- Has excellent knows of Python and knows how to write effective SQL queries;
- Has knowledge of basic mathematics, probability theory, and applied statistics;
- Has knowledge of how standard Machine Learning algorithms work and has experience in their practical implementation and production support;
- Is able to explain their ideas to people who may not have knowledge of mathematics and machine learning, as well as independently convert a business problem into an algorithmic one;
- Is able to propose metrics for optimization and different methods for solving the problem;
- Likes to work in a team and takes the initiative when necessary.

**Условия**
•	Employment type: Remote
	•	Paid time off: Vacation days and day-offs are provided
	•	Sick leave: Covered
	•	Growth opportunities: Available within the team and company
	•	Contract: Formal agreement outlining all terms and responsibilities

